revisions.description: PTP650-01-40: Added Second Data Service attributes to support a second data path over wireless link. Added support for Cable Diagnostics. Added IEEE 1588 Transparent Clock source port and Transparent Clock source alarm attributes.

PTP650-01-20: Added TDM group and NIDU attributes to support the telecomms interfaces. Added Router Protocols group to support Microwave Adaptive Bandwidth (MAB). Added support for Out-Of-Band Remote Management, and for mute and enable transmission. Renamed 'ethernet bridging' attributes to 'data bridging'. Made more SyncE attributes writable.

PTP650-01-10: Added Synchronous Ethernet (SyncE) and IEEE 1588 Transparent Clock. Support PTP650s. Clarified localPacketFiltering, regulatoryBand, TDD Sync status & alarm. TX power max increased to 30dBm. Modified the bit assignments of enabledDiagnosticAlarms to combine the various status & warning bits for the main PSU, Aux & SFP ports into a single portState bit.

mainPSUPortAutoNegotiation.description: This controls whether the local Ethernet interface configuration is automatically negotiated or forced. licenseRemainingTrialPeriodAlarm.description: If the full capability trial license period is about to expire then purchase a license upgrade from your reseller.

capacityVariantMismatch.name: capacityVariantMismatch
capacityVariantMismatch.description: The remote node of this link has a lower link capacity. Operating with a reduced effective link capacity.

licenseTDDSyncSupport.name: licenseTDDSyncSupport
licenseTDDSyncSupport.description: The license key TDD Synchronization support setting.

licenseMaxLinkRange.name: licenseMaxLinkRange
licenseMaxLinkRange.description: Maximum licensed range for the wireless link in tenths of km. A value of zero indicates that the maximum link range is not limited by the license.

licenseTrialPeriod.name: licenseTrialPeriod
licenseTrialPeriod.description: The license key maximum trial period, in days.

licenseRARSupport.name: licenseRARSupport
licenseRARSupport.description: The license key Radio Aware Routing support setting.

licenseRegulatoryBandsTableIndex.name: licenseRegulatoryBandsTableIndex
licenseRegulatoryBandsTableIndex.description: License regulatory bands, used to index the LicenseRegulatoryBandsTable.

licenseRegulatoryBandsList.name: licenseRegulatoryBandsList
licenseRegulatoryBandsList.description: The list of regulatory bands for which the unit is licensed to operate. A regulatory band prohibits the wireless unit from operating outside the regulated limits. An invalid regulatory band indicates a corrupted license key. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert.

targetRange.name: targetRange
targetRange.description: Initial target range used in installation +/-1, expressed in tenths of a kilometer. When Auto-Ranging this must be set to 0

rangingMode.name: rangingMode
rangingMode.description: Type of ranging to use during installation, either Auto-Ranging or use a selectable Target Range

installStatus.name: installStatus
installStatus.description: A non-zero value indicates that signalling was received with the wrong MAC address or a mismatched link name. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because units with mis-configured Target MAC Address will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, rare circumstances may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value on start-up, or a change of value during operation, may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

installArmState.name: installArmState
installArmState.description: Indicates if the unit is being installed. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

tFTPServerPortNumber.name: tFTPServerPortNumber
tFTPServerPortNumber.description: The port number of the TFTP Server from which the TFTP Software Upgrade File Name will be retrieved

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName.description: Filename of the Software Upgrade to be loaded from the TFTP Server

tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade.name: tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade
tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade.description: Write '1' to this attribute to start the TFTP software upgrade process. The attribute will be reset to 0 when the upgrade process has finished. Continuing with the software upgrade will cause spectrum management (DSO) channel metrics collection to stop. The wireless unit will no longer search for the optimal operational radio channel. The performance of this wireless link may deterioate over time. If operating in a regulatory band where RADAR detection is mandatory you must complete the software upgrade and reboot the unit. Channel metrics collection will only be restarted after the wireless unit has been rebooted

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus.description: The current status of the TFTP Software upgrade process

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText.description: Descriptive text describing the status of the TFTP Software upgrade process, including any error details

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText.description: Any additional text describing the status of the TFTP Software upgrade process, including any error details

hTTPAccessEnabled.name: hTTPAccessEnabled
hTTPAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not HTTP access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the HTTP port. Remote management via HTTPS is not affected by this setting. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Enabled)

telnetAccessEnabled.name: telnetAccessEnabled
telnetAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not Telnet access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the TELNET port. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Disabled)

hTTPPortNumber.name: hTTPPortNumber
hTTPPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for HTTP access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 80)

hTTPSPortNumber.name: hTTPSPortNumber
hTTPSPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for HTTPS access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Availability of HTTPS is controlled via the License Key. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 443)

telnetPortNumber.name: telnetPortNumber
telnetPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for TELNET access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 23)

hTTPSAccessEnabled.name: hTTPSAccessEnabled
hTTPSAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not HTTPS access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the HTTPS port. Remote management via HTTP is not affected by this setting. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Enabled)

tFTPServerInternetAddressType.name: tFTPServerInternetAddressType
tFTPServerInternetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address specified by the associated tFTPServerInternetAddress.

tFTPServerInternetAddress.name: tFTPServerInternetAddress
tFTPServerInternetAddress.description: INET address of the TFTP Server from which the TFTP Software Upgrade File Name will be retrieved

lowestDataModulationMode.name: lowestDataModulationMode
lowestDataModulationMode.description: The lowest modulation mode at which Ethernet Data traffic will be bridged over the wireless link

lowestSecondDataModulationMode.name: lowestSecondDataModulationMode
lowestSecondDataModulationMode.description: The lowest modulation mode at which Second Data Service Ethernet traffic will be bridged over the wireless link

linkSymmetry.name: linkSymmetry
linkSymmetry.description: Provides configuration options for sharing the available wireless capacity between the transmit and receive directions. Fixed link symmetry is defined by a ratio of the burst duration for the transmit direction to the burst duration for the receive direction. Permitted settings are 5:1, 3:1, 2:1, 1:1, 1:2, 1:3, 1:5. The 1:1 option provides fixed symmetric operation. The adaptive option selects transmit and receive burst durations automatically in response to the offered Ethernet traffic in each link direction. This attribute is valid only for a unit configured as a TDD Master

userConfiguredMaxModulationMode.name: userConfiguredMaxModulationMode
userConfiguredMaxModulationMode.description: The maximum receive modulation mode controls the MAX mode used for adaptive modulation. NOTE: This attribute is automatically disabled when the installation agent is armed. To disarm the installation agent use the installation wizard

linkModeOptimization.name: linkModeOptimization
linkModeOptimization.description: Optimizes the wireless link behavior for the type of traffic to be carried. In 'IP Traffic' mode, the wireless link will minimize transmission errors by automatically adapting the modulation mode. In 'TDM Traffic' mode, the wireless link will minimize transmission latency and preserve throughput by maintaining a higher modulation mode in the presence of a limited number of errors. The 'TDM Traffic' mode is recommended for E1/T1 applications and connectionless protocols.

txColorCode.name: txColorCode
txColorCode.description: Transmit Color Code. This attribute need only be considered when the unit is installed in a network of PTP units and where some of the units are operating on the same frequency. In this case, the value would normally be derived by a network planner. In all other cases, it is recommended that this attribute is left at the default value. NOTE: For the link to operate, the value of this parameter must in all cases match the value of the Rx Color Code parameter at the far end of the link.

rxColorCode.name: rxColorCode
rxColorCode.description: Receive Color Code. This attribute need only be considered when the unit is installed in a network of PTP units and where some of the units are operating on the same frequency. In this case, the value would normally be derived by a network planner. In all other cases, it is recommended that this attribute is left at the default value. NOTE: For the link to operate, the value of this parameter must in all cases match the value of the Tx Color Code parameter at the far end of the link.

remoteMaximumTransmitPower.name: remoteMaximumTransmitPower
remoteMaximumTransmitPower.description: Maximum transmit power the remote wireless unit is permitted to use when establishing and maintaining the wireless link

linkLoss.name: linkLoss
linkLoss.description: The wireless link loss expressed in tenths of a dB

receivePower.name: receivePower
receivePower.description: Receive power expressed in tenths of a dBm

vectorError.name: vectorError
vectorError.description: The vector error measurement compares the received signal's IQ modulation characteristics to an ideal signal to determine the composite error vector magnitude. The value represented by this attribute is the average vector error over the previous second expressed in tenths of a dB

transmitPower.name: transmitPower
transmitPower.description: Transmit power expressed in tenths of a dBm

receiveFreqMHz.name: receiveFreqMHz
receiveFreqMHz.description: Current receive frequency expressed in integer MHz

transmitFreqMHz.name: transmitFreqMHz
transmitFreqMHz.description: Current transmit frequency expressed in integer MHz

signalStrengthRatio.name: signalStrengthRatio
signalStrengthRatio.description: Signal strength ratio (Vertical / Horizontal) : the number of dB larger the Vertical antenna input is than the Horizontal antenna input expressed in tenths of a dB

receiveFreqKHz.name: receiveFreqKHz
receiveFreqKHz.description: Current receive frequency expressed as KHz

transmitFreqKHz.name: transmitFreqKHz
transmitFreqKHz.description: Current transmit frequency expressed as KHz

rawReceivePower.name: rawReceivePower
rawReceivePower.description: Raw receive power expressed in tenths of a dBm

range.name: range
range.description: Distance between the two peer wireless units expressed in tenths of a kilometer

searchState.name: searchState
searchState.description: Search status of the wireless modem. 'Registering' means that the modem has locked to an OFDM signal, and the wireless link is up. 'Searching' means that no wireless signal has been detected. 'Acquiring' means that a wireless signal has been detected, but the modem has not locked to an OFDM signal.

unitOutOfCalibration.name: unitOutOfCalibration
unitOutOfCalibration.description: The unit is out of calibration

incompatibleRegulatoryBands.name: incompatibleRegulatoryBands
incompatibleRegulatoryBands.description: The master and slave units have incompatible regulatory bands. NB: Both units must have compatible license keys

noWirelessChannelAvailable.name: noWirelessChannelAvailable
noWirelessChannelAvailable.description: Spectrum Management was unable to locate a suitable wireless channel to operate on

wirelessLinkDisabledWarning.name: wirelessLinkDisabledWarning
wirelessLinkDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the wireless interface has disabled wireless traffic

mainPSUPortDisabledWarning.name: mainPSUPortDisabledWarning
mainPSUPortDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

sFPError.name: sFPError
sFPError.description: If the SFP link is not OK, there are five possible causes: Either a SFP has been installed but the license key does not include SFP fiber support, a fiber link could not be established even though no LOS was detected (i.e. an optical carrier was detected, which could be due to a broken TX fiber, or because the link is disabled at the fiber link partner), a fiber link could not be established and LOS is detected (i.e. no optical carrier is detected), the installed SFP is not supported or the installed SFP failed to initialize correctly. NB: a change of status may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

mainPSUPortConfigurationMismatch.name: mainPSUPortConfigurationMismatch
mainPSUPortConfigurationMismatch.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch

incompatibleMasterAndSlave.name: incompatibleMasterAndSlave
incompatibleMasterAndSlave.description: A non-zero value indicates that the master and slave ends of a link are different hardware products, or have different software versions. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because incompatible units will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, some combinations may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

tDDSynchronizationStatus.name: tDDSynchronizationStatus
tDDSynchronizationStatus.description: An alarm value (displayed in red) indicates that one of the following conditions has not been met (i) An external timing system is connected or internal timing has been configured. (ii) The timing system is providing a useable reference. (iii) The ODU is locked to this reference.

auxPortDisabledWarning.name: auxPortDisabledWarning
auxPortDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

tDDSynchronizationAlarm.name: tDDSynchronizationAlarm
tDDSynchronizationAlarm.description: Not Synchronized indicates failure of the external timing system for a period greater than the holdover timer. TDD frame timing will have drifted, and this link may cause interference with other links in a synchronized network. Timing System Failure is an early warning, indicating that 80% of the holdover period has expired.

linkModeOptimizationMismatch.name: linkModeOptimizationMismatch
linkModeOptimizationMismatch.description: The remote node of this link has been configured with a different link mode optimization

auxPortConfigurationMismatch.name: auxPortConfigurationMismatch
auxPortConfigurationMismatch.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch. This alarm is only raised if an Out-of-Band Management Mode has been configured.

secureModeAlarm.name: secureModeAlarm
secureModeAlarm.description: The secure mode (e.g. FIPS, UC-APL) state of the unit. The secure mode is not configured(1) state indicates that the unit is capable of secure mode operation, and one or more of the following security materials has not been configured: Key Of Keys, Private Key, Public Certificate, DRNG Entropy Status, Wireless Encryption Key. The secure mode mode is configured but not active(2) state indicates that the unit is capable of secure mode operation, and the security material has been configured, but the configuration of interfaces is not consistent with secure mode operation. The secure mode is not supported(3) state indicates that the unit is not capable of secure mode operation. The secure mode capability requires appropriate hardware compatibility, license key and software image.

dataBridgingStatusAlarm.name: dataBridgingStatusAlarm
dataBridgingStatusAlarm.description: Ethernet Data traffic bridging is disabled because the wireless link is not operating at the configured Lowest Data Modulation Mode

sFPPortDisabledWarning.name: sFPPortDisabledWarning
sFPPortDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

sFPPortConfigurationMismatch.name: sFPPortConfigurationMismatch
sFPPortConfigurationMismatch.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch. This alarm is only raised if an Out-of-Band Management Mode has been configured.

maxLinkRangeExceeded.name: maxLinkRangeExceeded
maxLinkRangeExceeded.description: The measured link range is greater than the maximum allowed by the license key. The link will operate at a reduced capacity while this condition applies. This alarm is only raised if the license specifies a maximum link range and the trial license is not active.

nIDULanPortDisabledWarning.name: nIDULanPortDisabledWarning
nIDULanPortDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

nIDULanPortConfigurationMismatch.name: nIDULanPortConfigurationMismatch
nIDULanPortConfigurationMismatch.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch.

portAllocationMismatch.name: portAllocationMismatch
portAllocationMismatch.description: The local and remote ODUs have different services configured.

secondDataBridgingStatusAlarm.name: secondDataBridgingStatusAlarm
secondDataBridgingStatusAlarm.description: Bridging of Ethernet traffic from Second Data Service has been disabled because the wireless link is not operating at the configured Lowest Second Data Modulation Mode

transparentClockSourcePortAlarm.name: transparentClockSourcePortAlarm
transparentClockSourcePortAlarm.description: Transparent Clock will not function properly because SFP, the selected clock source port is not FIBER

sMTPEmailAlert.name: sMTPEmailAlert
sMTPEmailAlert.description: Simple Mail Transfer Protocol is used to send equipment alerts via email to a specified email address

sMTPServerPortNumber.name: sMTPServerPortNumber
sMTPServerPortNumber.description: Port number of the SMTP server

sMTPSourceEmailAddress.name: sMTPSourceEmailAddress
sMTPSourceEmailAddress.description: The 'from' email address used when constructing the automatically generated e-mail message

sMTPDestinationEmailAddress.name: sMTPDestinationEmailAddress
sMTPDestinationEmailAddress.description: The 'to' email address used when constructing the automatically generated e-mail message

sMTPEnabledMessages.name: sMTPEnabledMessages
sMTPEnabledMessages.description: This controls which SMTP messages the unit will send

sMTPServerInternetAddressType.name: sMTPServerInternetAddressType
sMTPServerInternetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address specified by the associated sMTPServerInternetAddress.

sMTPServerInternetAddress.name: sMTPServerInternetAddress
sMTPServerInternetAddress.description: Internet address of the SMTP server

sNMPPortNumber.name: sNMPPortNumber
sNMPPortNumber.description: The IP port number used to access the SNMP MIB (i.e. Gets and Sets) (default = 161). NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPCommunityString.name: sNMPCommunityString
sNMPCommunityString.description: The SNMP community string. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPTrapTableNumber.name: sNMPTrapTableNumber
sNMPTrapTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the sNMPTrapTable.

sNMPTrapVersion.name: sNMPTrapVersion
sNMPTrapVersion.description: The SNMP protocol version to use for SNMP Traps. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPEnabledTraps.name: sNMPEnabledTraps
sNMPEnabledTraps.description: This controls which SNMP Traps the unit will send

enabledDiagnosticAlarms.name: enabledDiagnosticAlarms
enabledDiagnosticAlarms.description: Controls which individual diagnostic alarms are enabled. The unit may be configured to generate SNMP traps and/or SMTP email alerts for these enabled alarms by selecting 'Enabled Diagnostic Alarms' on the 'SNMP Enabled Traps' and/or 'SMTP Enabled Messages' attributes

sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup.name: sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup
sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup.description: Controls whether cleared traps are reported at start-up as well as raised traps. Only enabled traps will be reported. NB: Traps corresponding to transient events (i.e. not associated with an alarm or status value) are only sent when required and not at start-up.

sNMPTrapTableIndex.name: sNMPTrapTableIndex
sNMPTrapTableIndex.description: SNMP trap value, used to index the SNMPTrapTable.

sNMPTrapPortNumber.name: sNMPTrapPortNumber
sNMPTrapPortNumber.description: Destination port for SNMP Traps (default=162). NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute.

sNMPTrapInternetAddressType.name: sNMPTrapInternetAddressType
sNMPTrapInternetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address specified by the associated sNMPTrapInternetAddress.

sNMPTrapInternetAddress.name: sNMPTrapInternetAddress
sNMPTrapInternetAddress.description: The Internet address to which all SNMP Traps are sent.

sNMPTrapReceiverEnabled.name: sNMPTrapReceiverEnabled
sNMPTrapReceiverEnabled.description: A value of 0 disables the sending of SNMP trap to corresponding receiver. A value of 1 enables the sending of SNMP trap to corresponding receiver.

sNTPSync.name: sNTPSync
sNTPSync.description: If SNTP Sync fails then check the server settings in the Remote Management page, or disable SNTP

systemClock.name: systemClock
systemClock.description: System clock presented as local time

timeZone.name: timeZone
timeZone.description: Time zone offsets from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT)

sNTPPrimaryServer.name: sNTPPrimaryServer
sNTPPrimaryServer.description: Specifies the primary SNTP server, determining the order in which the servers are tried.

sNTPPrimaryServerDeadTime.name: sNTPPrimaryServerDeadTime
sNTPPrimaryServerDeadTime.description: Time (in seconds) to wait before retrying communications with an unresponsive primary SNTP server. Setting the value to 0 disables the timer.

sNTPServerRetries.name: sNTPServerRetries
sNTPServerRetries.description: Number of times the PTP will retry after an SNTP server fails to respond.

sNTPServerTimeout.name: sNTPServerTimeout
sNTPServerTimeout.description: Time (in seconds) the PTP will wait for a response from an SNTP server.

sNTPServerTableNumber.name: sNTPServerTableNumber
sNTPServerTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the SNTPServerTable.

sNTPServerPortNumber.name: sNTPServerPortNumber
sNTPServerPortNumber.description: The IP port number of the SNTP server. Defaults to port 123.

sNTPServerStatus.name: sNTPServerStatus
sNTPServerStatus.description: Status message reflecting the result of communications with the SNTP server when last polled

sNTPServerInternetAddressType.name: sNTPServerInternetAddressType
sNTPServerInternetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address specified by the associated sNTPServerInternetAddress.

sNTPServerInternetAddress.name: sNTPServerInternetAddress
sNTPServerInternetAddress.description: The Internet address of a valid SNTP server

systemReset.name: systemReset
systemReset.description: Setting this attribute to '1' will cause a system reboot. NB: a system reboot will apply any pending new settings held in memory

secondarySoftwareVersion.name: secondarySoftwareVersion
secondarySoftwareVersion.description: Secondary software version, used when the primary software image is invalid or erased

receiveDataRate.name: receiveDataRate
receiveDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

transmitDataRate.name: transmitDataRate
transmitDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

aggregateDataRate.name: aggregateDataRate
aggregateDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

wirelessLinkAvailability.name: wirelessLinkAvailability
wirelessLinkAvailability.description: Link availability calculated since the last reset of the system counters, as a percentage multiplied by 10000 to give four decimal places of precision

wirelessLinkStatus.name: wirelessLinkStatus
wirelessLinkStatus.description: Current status of the wireless link

byteErrorRatio.name: byteErrorRatio
byteErrorRatio.description: Reciprocal of the byte error ratio calculated since the last reset of the system counters

receiveModulationModeDetail.name: receiveModulationModeDetail
receiveModulationModeDetail.description: The reason for the current receive modulation mode

dataBridgingAvailability.name: dataBridgingAvailability
dataBridgingAvailability.description: Link availability bridging Ethernet Data traffic calculated since the last reset of the system counters, as a percentage multiplied by 10000 to give four decimal places of precision

encryptionAlgorithm.name: encryptionAlgorithm
encryptionAlgorithm.description: The Encryption Algorithm used by the wireless link. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute. NB: The same Encryption Algorithm must be configured at BOTH ends of the link for it to function correctly

userTableNumber.name: userTableNumber
userTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the userTable

userTableIndex.name: userTableIndex
userTableIndex.description: used to index values in the userTable.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: User name which must be entered, along with the appropriate password, in order to gain access to the system.

userRole.name: userRole
userRole.description: Role of the selected user. A Security Officer has access to and can modify all settings. A System Administrator has access to and can modify all non-security settings. A Read Only user can view settings, but cannot make any changes.

userPassword.name: userPassword
userPassword.description: User password, which must be entered in order to gain access to the system.

syslogClient.name: syslogClient
syslogClient.description: Enable or disable the syslog client

syslogState.name: syslogState
syslogState.description: The syslog service has been enabled or disabled

microwaveAdaptiveBandwidth.name: microwaveAdaptiveBandwidth
microwaveAdaptiveBandwidth.description: Enable support of Microwave Adaptive Bandwidth Protocol. MAB is disabled if link symmetry is configured as Adaptive

mABNominalModulationMode.name: mABNominalModulationMode
mABNominalModulationMode.description: The Nominal modulation mode is the desired modulation mode. MAB VSM packets are generated when the current modulation mode falls below the nominal modulation.

mABTransmissionInterval.name: mABTransmissionInterval
mABTransmissionInterval.description: The minimum interval (in seconds) between successive MAB vendor specific messages (VSM). These VSM are sent when the current transmit capacity falls below the configured MAB Nominal Modulation Mode.

mABHoldoffPeriod.name: mABHoldoffPeriod
mABHoldoffPeriod.description: The period (in seconds) over which transmit capacity is averaged over to determine when the wireless link has degraded

mABMaintenanceLevel.name: mABMaintenanceLevel
mABMaintenanceLevel.description: Maintenance Levels (0-7) determines the destination MAC address of MAB vendor specific messages.

useVLANForMABProtocol.name: useVLANForMABProtocol
useVLANForMABProtocol.description: This controls whether MAB vendor specific messages (VSM) packets use VLAN tags or not.

mABProtocolVID.name: mABProtocolVID
mABProtocolVID.description: This VLAN VID (0-4094) will be included in MAB vendor specific messages (VSM) packets.

mABProtocolVLANPriority.name: mABProtocolVLANPriority
mABProtocolVLANPriority.description: This VLAN Priority (0-7) will be included in MAB vendor specific messages (VSM) packets.

mABState.name: mABState
mABState.description: Current state of MAB Protocol. A state of 'Normal' on a green background indicates that a PTP link is operating at nominal capacity

mABNominalTransmitCapacity.name: mABNominalTransmitCapacity
mABNominalTransmitCapacity.description: The nominal Tx capacity used in MAB Vendor Specific Messages for the selected nominal modulation mode

mABCurrentTransmitCapacity.name: mABCurrentTransmitCapacity
mABCurrentTransmitCapacity.description: The current Tx capacity of the wireless link used in the last MAB Vendor Specific Message transmitted.

cableDiagnosticsPorts.name: cableDiagnosticsPorts
cableDiagnosticsPorts.description: Select ports on which Cable Diagnostics must be executed

cableDiagnosticsControl.name: cableDiagnosticsControl
cableDiagnosticsControl.description: Set this attribute to 'Test in Progress' to start a Cable Diagnostics test

cableDiagnosticsWarning.name: cableDiagnosticsWarning
cableDiagnosticsWarning.description: Normal Ethernet operation is disrupted when a Cable Diagnostics test is in progress

cableDiagnosticsResultTableNumber.name: cableDiagnosticsResultTableNumber
cableDiagnosticsResultTableNumber.description: Number of rows in the Cable Diagnostics Result Table.

cableDiagnosticsResultTableIndex.name: cableDiagnosticsResultTableIndex
cableDiagnosticsResultTableIndex.description: Cable Diagnostics Port value used to index into the result table.

cableDiagnosticsResultsDateTime.name: cableDiagnosticsResultsDateTime
cableDiagnosticsResultsDateTime.description: The Date and Time when a Cable Diagnostics test was last executed

cableDiagPair1Results.name: cableDiagPair1Results
cableDiagPair1Results.description: The result of the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics on cable pair 1. According to the T658B wiring scheme, pair 1 is pins 4 & 5 on the RJ45 socket on the ODU. Open Circuit is reported when the impedance is greater than 330 ohms. Short Circuit is reported when the impedance is less than 33 ohms. Unknown is reported when a continuous signal is received from the link partner for 125 ms, preventing start of the test.

cableDiagPair1Distance.name: cableDiagPair1Distance
cableDiagPair1Distance.description: The distance in meters from the ODU to the fault detected on the cable pair during the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics. Faults in cables longer than 160 meters (525 feet) may not be detected. The error margin is +/-2 meters (6.5 feet).

cableDiagPair2Results.name: cableDiagPair2Results
cableDiagPair2Results.description: The result of the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics on cable pair 2. According to the T658B wiring scheme, pair 2 is pins 1 & 2 on the RJ45 socket on the ODU. Open Circuit is reported when the impedance is greater than 330 ohms. Short Circuit is reported when the impedance is less than 33 ohms. Unknown is reported when a continuous signal is received from the link partner for 125 ms, preventing start of the test.

cableDiagPair2Distance.name: cableDiagPair2Distance
cableDiagPair2Distance.description: The distance in meters from the ODU to the fault detected on the cable pair during the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics. Faults in cables longer than 160 meters (525 feet) may not be detected. The error margin is +/-2 meters (6.5 feet).

cableDiagPair3Results.name: cableDiagPair3Results
cableDiagPair3Results.description: The result of the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics on cable pair 3. According to the T658B wiring scheme, pair 3 is pins 3 & 6 on the RJ45 socket on the ODU. Open Circuit is reported when the impedance is greater than 330 ohms. Short Circuit is reported when the impedance is less than 33 ohms. Unknown is reported when a continuous signal is received from the link partner for 125 ms, preventing start of the test.

cableDiagPair3Distance.name: cableDiagPair3Distance
cableDiagPair3Distance.description: The distance in meters from the ODU to the fault detected on the cable pair during the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics. Faults in cables longer than 160 meters (525 feet) may not be detected. The error margin is +/-2 meters (6.5 feet).

cableDiagPair4Results.name: cableDiagPair4Results
cableDiagPair4Results.description: The result of the most recent execution of Cable Diagnostics on cable pair 4. According to the T658B wiring scheme, pair 4 is pins 7 & 8 on the RJ45 socket on the ODU. Open Circuit is reported when the impedance is greater than 330 ohms. Short Circuit is reported when the impedance is less than 33 ohms. Unknown is reported when a continuous signal is received from the link partner for 125 ms, preventing start of the test.
